# Lab Setup Guide

Complete steps to build this lab from scratch.

## Requirements

- Computer with 8GB+ RAM
- VMware Workstation Player (free)
- Kali Linux VM image
- Ubuntu ISO

## Step 1: Create Virtual Machines

### Ubuntu VM
1. Open VMware → Create New VM
2. Select Ubuntu ISO
3. Set 4GB RAM, 25GB disk
4. Install Ubuntu, create username and password
5. Restart when done

### Kali VM
1. Download from kali.org (VMware version)
2. File → Open → Select Kali .vmx file
3. Login: `kali` / `kali`

## Step 2: Check Network

### On Ubuntu
```bash
ip a
```
Note your IP (example: 192.168.115.129)

### On Kali
```bash
ip a
```
Note your IP (example: 192.168.115.128)

### Test Connection
```bash
ping 192.168.115.129
```

## Step 3: Install Tools on Ubuntu

```bash
# Update system
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

# Install web server
sudo apt install apache2 -y

# Install SSH server
sudo apt install openssh-server -y

# Install Wireshark
sudo apt install wireshark -y
sudo usermod -aG wireshark $USER

# Install firewall
sudo apt install ufw -y

# Restart
sudo reboot
```

## Step 4: Configure Firewall

```bash
sudo ufw enable
sudo ufw default deny incoming
sudo ufw default allow outgoing
sudo ufw allow 22
sudo ufw allow 80
sudo ufw status
```

## Lab Ready!

| Machine | IP | Role |
|---------|-----|------|
| Ubuntu | 192.168.115.129 | Defender |
| Kali | 192.168.115.128 | Attacker |

